# S05-T04: Swipe Panels

## Objective
Edge-swipe gestures to show/hide HUD slot groups (left = telemetry panel, right = settings, top = top-bar, bottom = graphs).

## Acceptance Criteria
- Edge-detection: gesture begins within 20px of viewport edge.
- Direction matched to slot group (left swipe-in ⇒ left panel).
- Slide animation: 200ms ease-out, translateX only.
- Persistence: open/closed state in `useLayoutStore`.

## Steps
1. Add edge-swipe recognizer to gesture engine.
2. Map directions ↔ slot groups.
3. Implement `<SidePanel>` wrapper with Framer Motion.
4. Persist last open/closed state per panel.

## Invariants
- Swipe never closes critical alert overlays.
- Panel widths fixed (320px); no responsive shrink.
- Animation strictly translateX (no scale/opacity composite).
